description:
File: lichen/subsys/lichen/app_interface/hal_bridge.c:187-196

The function calculates observed uptime as: now_ms - age_ms

  static int64_t observed_uptime_from_age_seconds(uint32_t age_seconds)
  {
      const int64_t now_ms = bridge_now_ms();
      ...
      const int64_t age_ms = bounded_age_seconds * 1000;
      return now_ms - age_ms;
  }

If age_seconds * 1000 > k_uptime_get(), this returns a negative value. Example:
- System uptime: 50 seconds (50000 ms)
- age_seconds: 100 (100000 ms)
- Result: -50000 ms (negative uptime!)

This negative value is then assigned at lines 356-358 and 446-448:
  sample.observed_uptime_ms_valid = true;
  sample.observed_uptime_ms = observed_uptime_from_age_seconds(app->age_seconds);

Downstream HAL code may not expect negative uptime values, causing undefined behavior or incorrect time calculations.

Fix: Clamp to 0 if the result would be negative, or validate age_seconds against current uptime before accepting.
